More and more forces mobilized for giant strike
The League of Trade Unions and the Hungarian Trade Union Federation are forming their coordination committee on Friday for the strike of indefinite duration, which begins on Monday.
On Saturday, a protest assembly will be held, on Monday - on the day of the People's Vote on the Health Insurance Act - the work stoppage begins.
Strike-related, significant traffic obstructions are expected, since the railway traffic is almost completely stopped, and the Budapest public transport companies (BKV) are also on strike until 13 o'clock.
Details of Monday's strike will be jointly announced by the League Unions and the Union Federation on Friday afternoon.
