A song from the album has even made it to the radio hit - the mr2 Petőfi, which broadcasts pop music from early to late, has gradually set the earworm to the listeners with the number "Wings of Love", which was recorded with the participation of six local singers ("Underground Divas").
Everything is okay (?).
The hvg.hu asked about Balázs Zságer.
hvg.hu: This new hit raises the question: To what extent is your music reserved for a certain layer?
Balázs Zságer: The term "shift music" doesn't exactly mean much to me.
In my opinion, there are two castes in pop music, not mainstream and underground, or alternative and pop, but commercial and honest.
Even the so-called alternative or underground music can be shallow and meaningless, but it can also only be produced for the sale that makes it commercial music.
Even a good pop number can come from an honest motif.
The listener’s willingness to accept also works according to this principle, independent of languages and national borders.
hvg.hu: Do you see a difference in the openness of the Hungarian and foreign audiences to your music?
B. Zs.: Abroad, especially west of us, pop music has a greater tradition.
Not only teenagers or twens go to concerts, but also the older audience.
They follow the trends in pop music that happen around them much more closely because they also consider them a part of contemporary culture.
hvg.hu: What role does the audience have in your work?
Is it important to see who, where, how many people listen to your music?
B. Zs.: Of course, it is a good feeling to see that more and more are coming to our concerts.
We never composed for the market.
With us, music is not created to serve a purpose, but for a reason.
The role of the audience is usually noticeable in the concerts, where there is already a mutual interaction, but these in turn exist only in the intangible changes of the moment.
Nevertheless, I noticed one thing: If you want to please everyone, you are no longer interesting.
hvg.hu: How far would you like to follow the example of Yonderboi?
He is on the road as a soloist and has built up his career rather in the West.
B. Zs.: We don’t really go his way, apart from the fact that you try again and again to interpret this into our music.
We see ourselves more as team players who trust in each other’s musical presence and let them unfold.
At first, of course, comparisons of our work with that of Yonderboi were inevitable, as several of us came out of his band and took a different path.
hvg.hu: In the charts of mr2 Petőfi, "Wings of Love" comes first.
Many have only heard the name Zagar in connection with this number.
Was the opening deliberately staged with a slightly more popular style towards a wider audience?
B. Zs.: We had no plans to write a hit, which should then be used as a draughtsman for the album.
This song is about more.
It was intended as the finale of the album, with which we wanted to resolve the sound orgy and the slightly more difficult themes.
hvg.hu: How did you choose the six singers?
Why them, what was the guiding principle?
B. Zs.: The basic idea was to make a gospel-like choir.
Then came the idea to assemble the choir from gifted soloists from the domestic music scene.
This is how the six-member choir was created - Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we then christened "Underground Divas".
hvg.hu: Did you want the song the same way, or did the girls help shape it?
B. Zs.: The number has been in the instrumental version for a long time, but when the material for the album was finished, we thought that this number still "needs something".
The chord sequence has formally demanded a singing voice.
I sang the tune the same night, later they learned the girls.
It all came practically right away and terrifyingly spontaneous.
I can remember, I was pretty electrified at the time, but it also took the "divas."
With my voice alone, the song would never have been so strong.
hvg.hu: Both on the record and at the concert, however, you had the impression that the girls were in the background.
There is no solo part (apart from the short solo of Judy Jay), they have no role of their own, sing completely together and are no louder than the music, so their singing is not only accompanied by the music.
They were also in the back of the stage.
Is it intentional?
B.Zs.: That they were in the back was so because of purely technical problems.
However, we deliberately did not want to give them solo roles.
The number is also about forgetting your ego a little, forgeting who came from where and where to go, we simply allow these certain wings, the wings of love to raise us.
I would like others to feel this euphoric state that we felt when the song was created.
hvg.hu: Which was the most elaborate song?
B. Zs.: In the musical work actually none at all, there have been more difficult tasks when mixing.
For example, "Dorian Gray's Dilemma", in which I play on a concert piano, or on "Rock'n'Roll Goes To The Girls", where the groove did not want to work for a long time, but gradually everything has come together, like a puzzle.
hvg.hu: What is your favorite number from the new album?
B. Zs.: This is constantly changing with the concerts and also now that I have "let go" of the album.
Currently it's "Prophet Is A Fool," "Escape From The Earth" and the number "Never The Same."
