The city administration handles around 2000 customers every day.
You have to queue for about half an hour.
In Prague, approx. 140000 drivers not yet exchanged their driver's license.
The issuance of a new driving licence lasts 20 days.
But it is possible to apply for the issue with a shortened period of five days.
In this case, however, the driver has to add 500 crowns.
Motorists who fail to make the prescribed exchange until the end of the year and drive off without a valid driver's license face a fine from January.
The culprit pays a maximum of 2000 crowns.
However, the police can also have it ended with an admonition during the transgression.
In the event of a transgression, the penalty can rise to 2500 kronor.
According to previous information, even those who do not drive at all can be imposed by the municipality.
He could, it was said, threaten a penalty of even 30000 crowns.
The ministry has already called on the offices to exercise mildness and to impose a maximum of 1000 crowns.
According to the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, but no one threatens a thousand crown punishment.
The driver’s license is a document in which everyone can decide whether they want to own it or not.
It is not an identity card that everyone must have, and indeed a valid one.
People who no longer want to drive should surrender their driver's license.
It is enough to take him to the competent municipal office or send him there by registered letter.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 will become invalid.
However, motorists will also have to gradually exchange other types of driving licences.
People with driving licences from 1994 to 2000 still have three years to exchange.
The validity of driving licences issued from 2001 to 2004 will end in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, this involves about 2.6 million other driver's licenses.
