Congress approves the MIFID directive, which was adopted on 1. November came into effect.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the Congress decision in the Senate on the additional/amendments related to the project, the government published the provisions that emerge from the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressional and Senate MPs, who in their negotiations and votes had the goal of establishing the best possible regulation, which ensures the safety of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneur activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market activity.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, MIFID, which is re-establishing the investment services regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, increasing the control claim of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive makes it possible to offer financial advice to both specialised companies and natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory firms that merge with the investment and brokerage companies of securities.
It also extends the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, so that the multilateral systems of the securities business and the systems for the internationalization of trading orders are added to the regulated circulation markets, which would eventually compete with the current economic operators.
The law obliges the investment companies to express the priorities of their company profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the control task of the CNMV.
The Economic Commission of Congress subsequently provided for further changes, with the decision that the debt bond, which is now subject to a high degree of risk to the investor, must now be considered “complex” financial resources, has been confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis. (U.S. Mortgage Crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the fields of work of qualified economists was used; 30 years after 1977 the regulation, which restricted the areas of work reserved for economists, was adopted.
For its part, the Senate set out new positions in the financial sector, how that of the business mediator, who works on foreign account, does not need authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for customer acquisition simultaneously to several investment companies.
The harmonised consumer price index (CPI) is up five-tenths in November and now stands at 4.1%.
The indicator, which is used for Eurostat to assess the rate of inflation within the European Union, provides the average price trend that occurred in Spain in November.
Its publication is in accordance with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which seeks a local and quality comparison to US products by disclosing the data.
The forecast for the indicator can be prepared prematurely by applying the same procedure as the harmonised consumer price index, but at the same time using various other statistical modeling methods to estimate the information that is not available at the time of the calculation.
However, the Spanish Bureau of Statistics (INE) warned that the early indicator only served as a benchmark, and therefore with the final result, which will be the next 14th. December is announced, does not have to agree.
