Which insurance is best for me?
The vehicle insurance, which covers a possible claim caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and used, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right vehicle insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is set out in writing by means of an insurance contract that stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding severance amount in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance company, which is composed of several factors, including Age, gender, time of creation of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or used.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accidents, higher contribution payments are also due.
For this reason, both over-25s and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, these tend to less accidents such as single persons.
The benefit attached to the vehicle impairs the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequently the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver must also thoroughly study the situation in order to select exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance company in order to be able to make not only a performance-based but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-priced insurance, such as the low driving experience and the “young” driver’s license.
Even if it were best for ideal insurance coverage to take out comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full-coverage comprehensive, so that the benefits of a fully comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the lower the amount to be paid," explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europe, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to your own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs; this will increase your credit by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit note is a reduction in the basic tariff at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase of said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalties depend on the company and its income.
If the company has had a profitable year, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments," explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving experience, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for a comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
“Normally, the young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving,” explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the “beginner’s fear” was removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not own children to take out comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person also allows.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly low their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a comprehensive insurance with deductible (with an amount around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit note, an extended insurance is recommended, which only starts for the third year of the vehicle.
“They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment,” Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full comprehensive insurance with a deductible (with an amount around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, one has to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accidental damage, but also because it entails high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
